<item>
 <title>Discussing the Questions</title>
 <link>http://archive.p2pu.org/introduction-finance-economics-mar-2010/discussion/discussing-questions-0</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;
1) Why do&amp;nbsp;countries have currencies with different values to each other?&lt;br /&gt;
Because of their monetary policy, this depends of the exchange rate regime, the way a country manages its currency in respect to foreign currencies and the foreign exchange market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2) How does a nation gain and / or lose when the value of their currency fluctuates?&lt;/p&gt;
